# Design System

Source of truth: [reference/Brand Guidelines.html](../../reference/Brand%20Guidelines.html). When in doubt about a color, gradient, or button spec, check that file (or its living Storybook recreation, `src/stories/foundations/BrandGuidelines.stories.tsx`) before guessing.

## Brand palette

| Token          | Hex       | Usage                                          |
|----------------|-----------|-------------------------------------------------|
| `red`          | `#A32705` | Primary brand accent — CTAs, links, eyebrows   |
| `red-deep`     | `#7E1D02` | Primary button hover fill, gradient dark stop  |
| `red-terra`    | `#C0532C` | Secondary/soft accent, gradient light stop     |
| `red-bright`   | `#B23A18` | Sheen-sweep gradient second stop (Key Moment CTA) |
| `vanilla`      | `#FFEEE4` | Secondary brand color — pale badges/icon bg, accent card bg |
| `cream`        | `#FFF3EC` | Warm off-white section background (deeper than lotion), plus hero/overlay tint |
| `lotion`       | `#FFFCFA` | Default light section background               |
| `ink`          | `#2B1A14` | Headline/heading text color                     |
| `charcoal`     | `#3D2D25` | Body copy text color                            |
| `muted-text`   | `#5C4A42` | Secondary/muted text (aka `ink-soft` on production pages) |
| `border-color` | `#EADFD8` | Borders, dividers                               |
| `white`        | `#FFFFFF` | Kept as-is                                      |

There is a single accent hue (burnt red) — the brand has no secondary color family. Use `red-terra` for softer/secondary emphasis instead of introducing a new hue.

Use Tailwind classes: `bg-red`, `text-red`, `bg-lotion`, `bg-vanilla`, `text-ink`, `text-muted-text`, `border-border-color`, etc. (mapped via `@theme inline` in `global.css`).

Gradients (CSS vars, max 2 per page per brand doc — reserve for hero/CTA moments):
- `--hero-gradient: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--red-deep) 0%, var(--red) 54%, var(--red-terra) 100%)` — hero/CTA/divider sections
- `--sheen-gradient: linear-gradient(100deg, var(--red), var(--red-bright))` — primary "Key Moment" CTA button fill

**Never** use `ink` or brand-`red` text on a gradient or `red` section background — use the warm near-white (`#FFF7F2`) / `vanilla` text pairing instead (see `[data-theme="red"|"gradient"]` in `global.css`).

## Typography

For heading weight/size specifics, `reference/pp-shared.css` and the reference page HTMLs (the live website mockups) are the source of truth — not `Brand Guidelines.html` (a separate print/PDF deliverable with its own heavier 500-weight scale for guideline-doc chrome).

- **Headings**: `font-serif` (Playfair Display Variable) — all `<h1>`–`<h4>` default to weight **400** (never bold/700), no letter-spacing by default. Heavier weights (500/600) are opt-in per component for smaller card/sub-headings (e.g. card titles), not the sitewide default.
- **Body**: `font-sans` (Plus Jakarta Sans Variable) — sitewide default weight is **300 (Light)**; headings/labels/buttons opt into heavier weights explicitly
- **Eyebrow**: 11px, 700 weight, `0.16em` letter-spacing, uppercase, `red` color — use `.eyebrow` class
- **Section titles**: use `.section-title` (Playfair 400, responsive clamp 30px–40px, matches reference `.h-section`)
- **Sub-section headings (h3)**: default rich-text "Heading 3" style is 26px mobile / 33px desktop, weight 500 — matches reference `.cms-step h3` / `.sol-copy-pane h3` / `.cas-copy-pane h3` (the large two-column feature-panel headers). Card-level titles (e.g. `cardTitle`, `SolutionCardGroup`) use their own smaller/larger sizes matched to their specific reference component — don't force them onto the generic h3 scale.
- **Subtitles**: use `.section-subtitle` (17px, 300 weight, `muted-text` color)

Inter is no longer loaded — Plus Jakarta Sans is the only sans in active use (self-hosted via `@fontsource-variable/plus-jakarta-sans`).

## Spacing tokens

Use `var(--space-*)` or Tailwind `spacing-*` (xs=8, sm=16, md=24, lg=48, xl=80, 2xl=120, 3xl=160).

Layout containers: `.pp-container` (max 1280px) and `.pp-container-narrow` (max 720px).
Section padding: `.pp-section` or `.pp-section-tight`.

## Module theme system

Every module section has a `theme` field in Sanity, driven by `themeField()` in `src/sanity/schemas/objects/theme.ts`: `"white"`, `"lotion"`, `"cream"`, `"vanilla"`, `"red"`, or `"gradient"`.

- `white` / `lotion` / `cream` / `vanilla` — light section rhythm (alternate these for visual variety); `cream` matches the pricing/step-band sections in `reference/Practice Performance Report.html` and `reference/Call Answering Solutions.html`
- `red` — bold solid-color accent section (use sparingly)
- `gradient` — reserved for hero/CTA moments only, max 2 per page

Apply via `data-theme` attribute on the section wrapper:

```tsx
<section data-theme={theme} style={{ background: "var(--section-bg)" }}>
```

CSS variables set per theme: `--section-bg`, `--section-text`, `--section-muted`, `--section-accent`.
`red` and `gradient` themes flip `.section-title`/`.eyebrow`/`.section-subtitle` to warm near-white + `vanilla` accent text (never `ink`/`red` on those backgrounds).

## Color enum fields (Sanity)

Several schema objects expose a color choice that maps to the single-accent system. Current enum values:

| Field | Options |
|---|---|
| `statCard.valueColor` | `ink` / `red` / `terra` / `muted` |
| `inlineStat.suffixColor` (cards/statRow, light bg only) | `red` / `terra` / `ink` |
| `statBandItem.suffixColor` (Stat Band, themed bands) | `accent` / `text` (theme-aware) / `red` / `terra` / `ink` (fixed) |
| `cardIcon.iconColor` | (custom `IconColorInput`) — `terra` default |
| `pricingCard.variant` | `light` (Lotion) / `dark` (Burnt Red) |
| `cardsBlock.cardTheme.cardBg` | `lotion` / `vanilla` / `white` / `transparent` |
| `statCardsBlock.theme` | `lotion` / `vanilla` / `white` |

`Navigation` has no `theme` field of its own — it's stateless and infers light/dark styling (logo variant, text color, scrolled bg) from whichever section's `theme` it's currently overlapping (the page's first module theme is passed in as `theme` prop; `red`/`gradient` → dark, everything else → light). See `Navigation.tsx`.

## Button hierarchy

1. **Primary/Key-Moment CTA**: `Button` (default variant, i.e. `variant="brand"` or omitted) — sheen-sweep gradient fill (`linear-gradient(100deg,var(--red),var(--red-bright))`), **white** text, 10–11px radius (rectangular, not pill), 600 weight, hover: lift + shadow (`0 6px 16px rgba(163,39,5,0.22)`) + white sheen sweep animation
2. **Secondary CTA**: `Button variant="outline"` — white bg, `red` text, `1.5px` border `rgba(163,39,5,0.28)`, hover fills to `vanilla` + border darkens to `0.40` opacity
3. **In-page secondary**: `.btn-secondary` — text-only variant used inline in raw-CSS contexts (not a `Button` component)
4. **Nav CTA**: `Button variant="nav"` — solid `red` fill, white text, `10px` radius rectangular pill-adjacent shape (not a full pill)

Use `size="cta"` for marketing/page-level CTA buttons (14px/28px padding, 14px type).

### Key button rules
- **Never** use `text-midnight`, `text-ink`, or navy/gold/teal-era classes on the primary button — it must be `text-white` on a `red`/gradient fill
- The primary button fill is a **gradient** (`sheen-sweep`), not a flat `red` — this is intentional per the brand doc's "Key Moment CTA" spec
- Secondary/outline buttons are white-filled with a translucent red border, not `border-warm-gray` (that token no longer exists)

## shadcn usage

- Install: `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`
- Config: `components.json` (style: `radix-vega`, aliases under `@/`)
- Installed: `button`, `card`, `badge`, `avatar`, `sheet`, `navigation-menu`
- Button has custom variants: `brand`/`default` (primary gradient), `nav`, `outline` (CTA-style) and size `cta`
- shadcn semantic tokens (`--primary`, `--secondary`, `--accent`, `--muted`, `--border`, etc.) are remapped to the brand palette in `global.css` — most `ui/*` primitives inherit brand colors automatically without a direct edit

## Animation

- `.reveal` / `.reveal-left` / `.reveal-right` + `.visible` for scroll-triggered entrance
- `.reveal-delay-{1..4}` for staggered children
- `RevealObserver` component handles intersection detection
- `[data-anim-header]` / `[data-anim-list]` — per-element progressive reveal for long sections (see `global.css` for stagger timing)

## Validating brand fidelity

`src/stories/foundations/BrandGuidelines.stories.tsx` is a living recreation of the web-relevant pages of `reference/Brand Guidelines.html` (colors, CTA buttons, ring motif, section backgrounds, CTA banner, stat callout), built from real components/tokens. Use it to visually diff any future brand/token change against the guideline doc. `src/stories/foundations/Button.stories.tsx` exercises the full `button.tsx` variant/size matrix — update it whenever a button variant changes.
